cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the problem of learning visual classifiers from textual descriptions, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed models use regression, domain transfer, and optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes a kernel function based on distributional semantics, which is a technique used in information retrieval (cs.IR).
